         </item-info>
         <ce:floats>
            <ce:figure id="f0005">
               <ce:label>Fig. 1</ce:label>
               <ce:caption id="ca0005">
                  <ce:simple-para id="sp0005" view="all">Sweden divided into geographical regions where regions 2, 3, and 4 (here called North, Mid, and South) were used as study areas because they cover the main distribution of <ce:italic>Goodyera repens</ce:italic> (inset photos show the evergreen leaf rosettes and flowering inflorescences).</ce:simple-para>
               </ce:caption>
               <ce:alt-text role="short" id="al0005">Fig. 1</ce:alt-text>
               <ce:link id="lk0005" locator="gr1" xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="pii:S000632072600073X/gr1" xlink:role="http://data.elsevier.com/vocabulary/ElsevierContentTypes/23.4"/>
            </ce:figure>
            <ce:figure id="f0010">
               <ce:label>Fig. 2</ce:label>
               <ce:caption id="ca0010">
                  <ce:simple-para id="sp0010" view="all">The occurrence probability of <ce:italic>Goodyera repens</ce:italic> over time (1993 to 2022) based on data from the Swedish national forest inventory. Points show the occupancy per year, whole line with 95% confidence intervals (grey) show model predictions, and broken line a Loess smoothing line.</ce:simple-para>
               </ce:caption>
               <ce:alt-text role="short" id="al0010">Fig. 2</ce:alt-text>
               <ce:link id="lk0010" locator="gr2" xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="pii:S000632072600073X/gr2" xlink:role="http://data.elsevier.com/vocabulary/ElsevierContentTypes/23.4"/>
            </ce:figure>
            <ce:figure id="f0015">
               <ce:label>Fig. 3</ce:label>
               <ce:caption id="ca0015">
                  <ce:simple-para id="sp0015" view="all">The occurrence probability in relation to region. Letters signify statistical differences.</ce:simple-para>
               </ce:caption>
               <ce:alt-text role="short" id="al0015">Fig. 3</ce:alt-text>
               <ce:link id="lk0015" locator="gr3" xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="pii:S000632072600073X/gr3" xlink:role="http://data.elsevier.com/vocabulary/ElsevierContentTypes/23.4"/>
            </ce:figure>
            <ce:figure id="f0020">
               <ce:label>Fig. 4</ce:label>
               <ce:caption id="ca0020">
                  <ce:simple-para id="sp0020" view="all">Distribution of basal area across plots (grey bars, left y-axis) and occurrence probability of <ce:italic>Goodyera repens</ce:italic> across basal area classes (dashed line, right y-axis), based on 28,405 inventories (<ce:italic>n</ce:italic> = 28,405) from 11,961 permanent plots. Note the different scales on the two y-axes.</ce:simple-para>
               </ce:caption>
               <ce:alt-text role="short" id="al0020">Fig. 4</ce:alt-text>
               <ce:link id="lk0020" locator="gr4" xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="pii:S000632072600073X/gr4" xlink:role="http://data.elsevier.com/vocabulary/ElsevierContentTypes/23.4"/>
            </ce:figure>
            <ce:table xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/cals/dtd" id="t0005" frame="topbot" rowsep="0" colsep="0">
               <ce:label>Table 1</ce:label>
               <ce:caption id="ca0025">
                  <ce:simple-para id="sp0025" view="all">Variables from the Swedish National Forest Inventory used for modelling occurrence probability and population dynamics of <ce:italic>Goodyera repens</ce:italic>. Several variables were processed to reduce the number of categories or to create new variables; details on how these processed variables were derived are provided in Table A1.</ce:simple-para>
               </ce:caption>
               <ce:alt-text role="short" id="al0025">Table 1</ce:alt-text>
               <tgroup cols="4">
                  <colspec colname="col1"/>
                  <colspec colname="col2"/>
                  <colspec colname="col3"/>
                  <colspec colname="col4"/>
                  <thead>
                     <row rowsep="1" valign="top">
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" colname="col1">Variable</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" colname="col2">Type (unit)</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" colname="col3">Categories or range</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" colname="col4">Original or processed</entry>
                     </row>
                  </thead>
                  <tbody>
                     <row>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" colname="col1">Plot ID</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" colname="col2"/>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" colname="col3"/>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" colname="col4">Original</entry>
                     </row>
                     <row>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" colname="col1">Year of inventory</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" colname="col2">Continuous (year)</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" colname="col3">1993–2022</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" colname="col4">Original</entry>
                     </row>
                     <row>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" colname="col1">Region</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" colname="col2">Categorical</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" colname="col3">2, 3, 4</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" colname="col4">Original</entry>
                     </row>
                     <row>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" colname="col1">Presence of peat</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" colname="col2">Categorical</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" colname="col3">0: no peat<br/>1: peat is present</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" colname="col4">Processed</entry>
                     </row>
                     <row>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" colname="col1">Moving soil water</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" colname="col2">Categorical</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" colname="col3">0: never or rarely<br/>1: shorter or longer periods</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" colname="col4">Processed</entry>
                     </row>
                     <row>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" colname="col1">Soil type</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" colname="col2">Categorical</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" colname="col3">0: no moraine<br/>1: moraine</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" colname="col4">Processed</entry>
                     </row>
                     <row>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" colname="col1">Soil depth</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" colname="col2">Categorical</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" colname="col3">0: shallow<br/>1: deep</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" colname="col4">Processed</entry>
                     </row>
                     <row>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" colname="col1">Bottom layer</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" colname="col2">Categorical</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" colname="col3">1: lichen type<br/>2: wetland moss type<br/>3: mesic moss type</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" colname="col4">Processed</entry>
                     </row>
                     <row>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" colname="col1">Field layer</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" colname="col2">Categorical</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" colname="col3">0: no bilberry (other)<br/>1: bilberry</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" colname="col4">Processed</entry>
                     </row>
                     <row>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" colname="col1">Ground inclination</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" colname="col2">Continuous (%)</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" colname="col3">2.5–70</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" colname="col4">Original</entry>
                     </row>
                     <row>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" colname="col1">Basal-area weighted mean height</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" colname="col2">Continuous (m)</entry>
